{
  "doc_id": "604",
  "text": "The main objective of the present study is to consider a combined unsteady-state bulk and directional phase transition process when the phase interface propagates in a binary supercooled/supersaturated mixture. The theory under consideration can also be used for the theoretical description of phase transition phenomena met in such systems as heterogeneous materials [CITATION_1] , ferroelectrics [CITATION_2] , terrestrial magma oceans and lava lakes [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , metastable colloids and magnetic fluids [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] and so on.",
